<p>Thank you for visiting depoclaimcenter.com (referred to as the "Website" or "Site"). This Privacy Policy is intended to inform you about the types of information we collect when you use our Website and the associated services ("Services"), including applications, widgets, and email notifications. The term "Depo Claim Center," "Email Agency," "we," "our," or "us" refers to depoclaimcenter.com. We may update this Privacy Policy periodically, so please review this page regularly to stay informed of any changes.</p>

<p><strong>Intended Audience:</strong><br>This Website and the Services are designed for U.S. residents only.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect and How We Use It</h2>
<p>We assist consumers in finding legal representation by connecting them with attorneys and law firms ("Service Providers"). We collect personally identifiable information (PII) that can identify you as an individual when you voluntarily provide this information, such as when you submit it through the Website. This information may include, but is not limited to, your first and last name, home address, telephone number, email address, date of birth, and health-related information relevant to your legal matter.</p>
<p>We use your PII for various lawful purposes, including:</p>
<p>– Delivering our services to you, including matching you with Service Providers.<br>
– Displaying customized content and advertising.<br>
– Conducting research and analysis to improve our services.<br>
– Ensuring the proper functioning of the Website.<br>
– Developing new services and features.<br>
– Alerting you to updates, information, and other communications relevant to your inquiry.<br>
– Responding to your requests for information.<br>
– Providing referrals to Service Providers, who may contact you using the information you provide.<br>
– Collecting additional information as needed.</p>

<p>We may also automatically gather certain information when you visit the Website, such as your IP address, browser type, internet service provider (ISP), referring/exit pages, operating system, date and time of visit, device type, clickstream data, and other activities on the Website. This information may be combined with other data we collect about you to improve the services we offer, enhance marketing efforts, analyze trends, and improve Website functionality.</p>

<h2>Sharing of Personal Information</h2>
<p><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> When you provide PII to us, we may share it with Service Providers (attorneys and law firms) to provide you with the legal referral you request and to allow them to contact you. Service Providers and other third parties may contact you by email, telephone, text message, postal mail, or other means.</p>
<p><strong>Corporate Affiliates:</strong> We may share the information collected on the Website with our subsidiaries, corporate affiliates, and related companies.</p>
<p><strong>Vendors and Suppliers:</strong> We may share your information with vendors and service providers for purposes such as verifying data and providing services like phone number verification and email distribution.</p>
<p><strong>Legal Rights and Obligations:</strong> We may disclose PII as required by law or in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including law enforcement requests and compliance with legal processes.</p>
<p><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of bankruptcy, merger, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as an asset of the Company.</p>

<h2>Consent to Marketing Communications</h2>
<p>By providing your telephone number on the Website, you consent to receive informational and marketing messages and telephone calls from us and our Service Providers. These communications may include automated calls, text messages, SMS, MMS, live and prerecorded calls, and more, even if your phone number is on a Do Not Call list. Consent is not required to obtain legal services, and message &amp; data rates may apply. You can revoke your consent at any time by contacting us.</p>

